news.title: Will appoint administrators if RWAs in Gurugram build illegal structures: DTCP
news.para: Gurugram's Department of Town and Country Planning (DTCP) demolished an illegal religious structure built by the former RWA of Suncity Avenue in Sector 102, following resident complaints. Officials noted a rising trend of RWAs undertaking unauthorized constructions in common areas, violating regulations.

news.title: Thane civic body orders survey of unauthorised constructions in Yeoor area adjoining SGNP
news.para: Thane Municipal Corporation has ordered a survey of illegal constructions in Yeoor. This follows concerns about commercial activities impacting the environment. The survey will identify unauthorized structures. Notices will be issued, followed by enforcement. A coordination committee will be formed. It includes officials from various departments and NGOs.

news.title: Gurugram civic body launches chatbot to provide property tax-related information
news.para: Gurugram residents can now access property tax details via a new chatbot service. The Municipal Corporation of Gurugram (MCG) introduced this service to share tax amounts and payment methods. Residents will receive information through phone calls and texts. This initiative aims to increase transparency and combat fraudulent payment demands.

news.title: Nashik civic body collects ₹100 crore in property tax in April-June
news.para: The Nashik Municipal Corporation (NMC) collected Rs 100 crore in property tax during the first quarter of the 2025-26 financial year, slightly less than the previous year's Rs 106 crore. This collection was supported by rebates offered for prompt payments, ranging from 6-8%.

news.title: Delhi CM urges Uttar Pradesh CM to help curb illegal sand mining in Yamuna river near border
news.para: Chief Minister Rekha Gupta has appealed to Uttar Pradesh CM Yogi Adityanath to urgently address illegal sand mining in the Yamuna River along the Delhi-UP border. Gupta highlighted the ecological damage, increased flood risk due to weakened embankments, and concerns raised by the National Green Tribunal.

news.title: NHB asks housing finance companies to pay interest on advance EMIs
news.para: The National Housing Bank (NHB) has mandated that housing finance companies (HFCs) must pay interest to borrowers on advance EMI payments held in sundry accounts, aligning with fair lending practices. NHB is also urging HFCs to prioritize borrower quality over advance collections to mitigate default risks.

news.title: No more building plan approvals needed for small plots in Prayagraj
news.para: Prayagraj residents can rejoice as the Uttar Pradesh Cabinet approves the Building Construction and Development Byelaws 2025. This allows construction on plots up to 100 sqm without prior plan approval, benefiting middle-class families by reducing costs and streamlining the building process.

news.title: Adani to execute MHADA’s largest-ever 142-acre redevelopment in Mumbai’s Motilal Nagar
news.para: MHADA and Adani Properties have partnered to redevelop Motilal Nagar in Goregaon, Mumbai, in MHADA's largest redevelopment project. Adani Properties will provide a significant portion of housing stock to MHADA, offering larger homes to existing residents and rehabilitating slum dwellers. This initiative aims to modernize housing infrastructure, address civic issues, and improve the quality of life for residents.

news.title: Delhi: DUSIB to clear its land of encroachments, provide housing to slum dwellers
news.para: Delhi Urban Shelter Improvement Board (DUSIB) is surveying its land to identify encroachments, mapping jhuggi jhopri clusters, and assessing land parcels for housing development. This initiative supports the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana, aiming to provide pucca housing to eligible slum dwellers.

news.title: Maharashtra: ‘One state one registration’ scheme faces delay over technical & legal concerns
news.para: The "one state one registration" scheme in Pune faces delays due to legal, technical, and administrative challenges, including fraud concerns and stamp duty evasion. While the initiative aims to streamline property registration, issues like impersonation and fraudulent land transfers have emerged as major roadblocks.

news.title: Over 300 defaulters set to lose Lucknow development body's flats
news.para: Lucknow Development Authority (LDA) is cancelling allotments for 338 defaulters who haven't fully paid for their flats, some paying as little as 40%. These units will be resold via 'first come, first served' and e-auction. Simultaneously, LDA is preparing to open registration for 72 new EWS flats in Dalibagh, built at a cost of Rs 5.5 crore.

news.title: Court rejects builder's plea over illegal work at Hyderabad’s Nandagiri Hills
news.para: A Hyderabad city court dismissed Net Net Ventures' plea against the GHMC's order to halt construction and remove deviations on their Nandagiri Hills site. The court emphasized the firm's "unclean hands" and lack of a prima facie case. This decision supports the GHMC's enforcement of building regulations after the firm's unsuccessful attempts to challenge the orders in higher courts.

news.title: Tamil Nadu RERA cracks down on flashy real estate ads with new rules
news.para: Tamil Nadu's real estate sector faces a reckoning as TNRERA cracks down on misleading advertisements. New regulations mandate clear display of RERA registration details, QR codes, and promoter information in all ads, across all media. Vague claims and inflated amenities are prohibited, ensuring buyers can verify project authenticity.

news.title: Gujarat records 245 new commercial projects in 2024-25
news.para: Gujarat's commercial real estate is rebounding strongly, marked by 245 new project launches in 2024-25, the highest since 2019-20. Unit registrations have also peaked post-Covid, reaching 31,520. Ahmedabad alone saw 72 projects, attracting significant investment. Green construction is gaining traction, driven by government incentives and buyer preferences for energy-efficient buildings.

news.title: Mahesh Babu gets consumer panel notice; actor named in fraud complaint over plot sale
news.para: Actor Mahesh Babu has been served a notice by a consumer court following a complaint against Sai Surya Developers, a real estate company he endorsed. A city-based doctor alleges she was defrauded of Rs 34.8 lakh after purchasing a non-existent plot, influenced by Mahesh Babu's endorsement.

news.title: Delhi HC issues notice to police on Gopal Ansal's plea to quash FIR
news.para: The Delhi High Court has issued a notice to the police regarding a cheating FIR against Gopal Ansal, who was convicted in the Uphaar fire tragedy case. The FIR was filed by a land buyer in an Ansal Buildwell Limited project, alleging non-delivery of property after payment.

news.title: DDA to auction residential plots in Vasant Kunj area
news.para: Delhi Development Authority will offer residential plots in Vasant Kunj. The project includes planning and demarcation of 118 plots. It also involves developing roads, sewage, and water infrastructure. The DDA will auction these plots later.

news.title: Lodha Developers clocks ₹44.5 billion pre-sales in Q1 FY26
news.para: Lodha Developers has a good start to fiscal year 2026. The company reports pre-sales of ₹44.5 billion in the first quarter. This reflects a 10% year-on-year growth. Five new projects are added across MMR, Pune and Bengaluru. The company is confident to achieve its annual pre-sales target. Collections reach ₹28.8 billion, a 7% increase.

news.title: Nagpur: 158 out of 212 commercial spaces by MahaMetro still vacant
news.para: Nagpur MahaMetro aims to increase revenue through commercial properties. Many spaces are currently vacant. Only 54 out of 212 units are leased. MahaMetro earned Rupees 137.81 crore in non-fare revenue last fiscal year. They project Rupees 178.12 crore this year. A Hilton hotel is planned near the Airport Metro station.
